00:49:45.440 --> 00:49:48.730 align:middle line:84%
and I wanted to talk to you
about the notion of using--

00:49:48.730 --> 00:49:50.700 align:middle line:84%
we talked about trauma
a couple of times--

00:49:50.700 --> 00:49:54.430 align:middle line:84%
but the notion of using
chanting through the process

00:49:54.430 --> 00:49:58.570 align:middle line:84%
of transition or death and
what this does, how this

00:49:58.570 --> 00:50:01.150 align:middle line:84%
is utilized, what it
does to the being who

00:50:01.150 --> 00:50:02.920 align:middle line:90%
is leaving this reality.

00:50:02.920 --> 00:50:06.460 align:middle line:84%
>>PURCE: There are so many
stories about sound in relation

00:50:06.460 --> 00:50:10.240 align:middle line:84%
to the passage, to death,
and choirs of angels.

00:50:10.240 --> 00:50:12.010 align:middle line:84%
I mean the interesting
thing about angels

00:50:12.010 --> 00:50:14.710 align:middle line:84%
is they don't come
in herds or packs.

00:50:14.710 --> 00:50:16.260 align:middle line:90%
They come in choirs.

00:50:16.260 --> 00:50:19.990 align:middle line:84%
So by very definition, their
whole nature is sonorous.

00:50:19.990 --> 00:50:24.580 align:middle line:84%
And the fact, I see them as
personified representations

00:50:24.580 --> 00:50:28.180 align:middle line:84%
of vibratory levels of
existence that exist

00:50:28.180 --> 00:50:30.310 align:middle line:90%
between the divine and us.

00:50:30.310 --> 00:50:33.750 align:middle line:84%
And in the Neoplatonic
tradition, a little bit of God

00:50:33.750 --> 00:50:36.220 align:middle line:84%
separates out, a little
bit of the soul substance

00:50:36.220 --> 00:50:39.010 align:middle line:84%
separates out from God and comes
down through the great chain

00:50:39.010 --> 00:50:42.190 align:middle line:84%
of being, finally through
the angels, the cherubim

00:50:42.190 --> 00:50:47.380 align:middle line:84%
and seraphim, and then comes
down to us through the elements

00:50:47.380 --> 00:50:48.730 align:middle line:90%
into a human being.

00:50:48.730 --> 00:50:51.760 align:middle line:84%
And then at the moment of
death, that separates out

00:50:51.760 --> 00:50:54.400 align:middle line:84%
and goes back through
the music of the spheres,

00:50:54.400 --> 00:50:58.000 align:middle line:84%
and we drop off all our
psychological blockages,

00:50:58.000 --> 00:51:02.670 align:middle line:84%
and configurations, and
return to the divine.

00:51:02.670 --> 00:51:05.500 align:middle line:84%
And Plato describes how
sitting on each of the spheres

00:51:05.500 --> 00:51:09.610 align:middle line:84%
is a musical being, a
bird-like creature, a siren,

00:51:09.610 --> 00:51:11.170 align:middle line:90%
uttering a different note.

00:51:11.170 --> 00:51:12.640 align:middle line:90%
So this passage between--

00:51:12.640 --> 00:51:16.190 align:middle line:84%
and they're called the
soul guides, psychopomps.

00:51:16.190 --> 00:51:20.140 align:middle line:84%
So in many traditions, this
journey between the worlds

00:51:20.140 --> 00:51:22.330 align:middle line:84%
has been described as
a sonorous one, both

00:51:22.330 --> 00:51:25.150 align:middle line:90%
coming in and going out.

00:51:25.150 --> 00:51:30.030 align:middle line:84%
And so in one of the things
I do are extended ceremonies.

00:51:30.030 --> 00:51:33.990 align:middle line:84%
I realize that it's important
not just to teach methods

00:51:33.990 --> 00:51:37.530 align:middle line:84%
of chanting in order to have
them as tools to overcome

00:51:37.530 --> 00:51:40.260 align:middle line:84%
separation, to get into
deep states of meditation,

00:51:40.260 --> 00:51:41.470 align:middle line:90%
and so on.

00:51:41.470 --> 00:51:43.410 align:middle line:84%
But actually to
provide situations

00:51:43.410 --> 00:51:46.260 align:middle line:84%
where people can,
for extended periods,

00:51:46.260 --> 00:51:49.660 align:middle line:84%
realize what happens
when you really do this.

00:51:49.660 --> 00:51:53.310 align:middle line:84%
And when you were
ceremonially, the key there

00:51:53.310 --> 00:51:54.440 align:middle line:90%
is that you have a witness.

00:51:54.440 --> 00:51:56.790 align:middle line:84%
So when you want to
change ourselves--

00:51:56.790 --> 00:51:59.400 align:middle line:84%
so people come to my workshops
because they think they could

00:51:59.400 --> 00:52:01.720 align:middle line:84%
be better, or kinder,
or more compassionate,

00:52:01.720 --> 00:52:03.189 align:middle line:90%
or develop their consciousness.

00:52:03.189 --> 00:52:04.980 align:middle line:84%
But then, they go home
and then the default

00:52:04.980 --> 00:52:08.100 align:middle line:84%
them sets in because
that's the them they always

00:52:08.100 --> 00:52:09.600 align:middle line:90%
know up to then.

00:52:09.600 --> 00:52:12.880 align:middle line:84%
So how do you sustain
the changes that happen?

00:52:12.880 --> 00:52:17.490 align:middle line:84%
And so what I found is that in
order to sustain the changes,

00:52:17.490 --> 00:52:18.600 align:middle line:90%
you need a witness.

00:52:18.600 --> 00:52:20.940 align:middle line:84%
And that's why if you
get married, for example,

00:52:20.940 --> 00:52:24.940 align:middle line:84%
traditionally, you have somebody
who signs a document and says,

00:52:24.940 --> 00:52:26.190 align:middle line:90%
I was here.

00:52:26.190 --> 00:52:29.430 align:middle line:84%
I saw, and I signed
this to say I was here,

00:52:29.430 --> 00:52:31.980 align:middle line:84%
which means that you
are now recognized

00:52:31.980 --> 00:52:33.450 align:middle line:90%
as being no longer unmarried.

00:52:33.450 --> 00:52:35.280 align:middle line:90%
You are now married.

00:52:35.280 --> 00:52:37.710 align:middle line:84%
And then you invite all your
friends and your families

00:52:37.710 --> 00:52:39.220 align:middle line:90%
to witness all those.

00:52:39.220 --> 00:52:41.280 align:middle line:84%
So nowadays, people have
destination weddings.

00:52:41.280 --> 00:52:43.925 align:middle line:84%
They go to exotic places
and get married underwater,

00:52:43.925 --> 00:52:45.300 align:middle line:84%
come back, and
tell their friends

00:52:45.300 --> 00:52:47.040 align:middle line:84%
and say, oh, by the
way we're married.

00:52:47.040 --> 00:52:48.059 align:middle line:90%
And they say, oh really?

00:52:48.059 --> 00:52:49.600 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: It was
already on Facebook.

00:52:49.600 --> 00:52:50.400 align:middle line:90%
So it's OK.

00:52:50.400 --> 00:52:51.940 align:middle line:90%
They're aware.

00:52:51.940 --> 00:52:52.900 align:middle line:90%
>>PURCE: Absolutely.

00:52:52.900 --> 00:52:55.050 align:middle line:84%
But the point about
the ceremonies

00:52:55.050 --> 00:52:57.860 align:middle line:84%
is that you have people
there as witnesses

00:52:57.860 --> 00:52:59.142 align:middle line:90%
so that there's no going back.

00:52:59.142 --> 00:53:00.600 align:middle line:84%
So you know that
they know that you

00:53:00.600 --> 00:53:03.280 align:middle line:84%
know that they know that
they're now no longer unmarried.

00:53:03.280 --> 00:53:04.080 align:middle line:90%
They're married.

00:53:04.080 --> 00:53:08.130 align:middle line:84%
And so they sustains them
in the new state of being,

00:53:08.130 --> 00:53:09.220 align:middle line:90%
and this is really key.

00:53:09.220 --> 00:53:12.720 align:middle line:84%
So in terms of working, I
find that working ceremonially

00:53:12.720 --> 00:53:14.310 align:middle line:84%
is essential for
this because then you

00:53:14.310 --> 00:53:17.330 align:middle line:84%
have all the people
witnessing your change.

00:53:17.330 --> 00:53:21.690 align:middle line:84%
And so I do these very
extended ceremonies.

00:53:21.690 --> 00:53:28.370 align:middle line:84%
And two of the ones that I do
